Let's skip forward to two expansions from now. Let's assume that the idea that you posted made it into the game.<br>
Now, the average amount of hitpoints of the exp-mobs for that expansion has been decided: it's gonna be 30k HP's. Also, the AA's for that expansion have been decided: Fire wizards are going to get a +100 percent to their damage. btw: previous expansion they already got a 6k fire-nuke. Now, two developers are going to decide how hard the &quot;base&quot; fire-nukes are going to hit: those fire-nukes that I, as a cold-based wizard, can use as well. <br>
Now, what they DON'T want, is 2 fire-based wizards pairing up and instakilling weak-to-fire mobs.<br>
<br>
So, what do you think. Will that fire-nuke in 2005 be balanced against your average, non-specialized wizard, or will it be balanced in such a way that we won't get Team Manaburn-like wizard duo's walking around?<br>
